init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But the government isn't giving it away for free.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: To get the drug, you and your friends decide to find a way into the headquarters of the government facility where it is supposedly being held.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They began their journey and successfully make it into the facility.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But it turns out there is an alarm.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They chose to continue and discover an elevator that leads to a secret floor deep within the building.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It was not to the lower floor, but to another section of the facility.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Then, the elevator stopped and the doors opened.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They were in a strange laboratory.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A few moments later, the doors opened and a mysterious figure walked in.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was the leader of the facility.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I will give you access, but you must agree to my terms."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You will bring me an item every week for the rest of your lives, and I will give you your drug.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If you do not, I will permanently seal off access to this facility."
